## Problem
While browsing through the TSDB append logic, I noticed a `TODO` left by `@codesome` in `tsdb/head_append.go` suggesting that we refactor `Commit()` to make it more readable:

https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/blob/main/tsdb/head_append.go#L1717

```go
// Commit writes to the WAL and adds the data to the Head.
// TODO(codesome): Refactor this method to reduce indentation and make it more readable.
func (a *headAppenderBase) Commit() (err error) {
```

I'd like to help clean this up as a good first issue!

I plan to refactor the Commit() function by pulling nested blocks into smaller helper functions or by using early returns where applicable to flatten the indentation and improve readability, as requested in the TODO.
